net.proteusframework.users.model

Class AcegiPermission

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.users.model.AcegiPermission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Entity<Long>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AllPermission

    @Entity
public class AcegiPermission
extends Object
implements Entity<Long>, Serializable, Cloneable
    Represents a permission that can be assigned to a Role. This class is similar in spirit to the java.security.Permission class, but is designed to integrate well with Acegi and Hibernate.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • implies

        public boolean implies(AcegiPermission permission)
        Checks if the specified permission's actions are "implied by" this object's actions.

        The implies method is used by the PermissionCheckProvider to determine whether or not a requested permission is implied by another permission.

        Parameters:
        permission - the permission to check against.
        Returns:
        true if the specified permission is implied by this object, false if not.
